
fantabulous (fan-TAB-yuh-luhs) adjective

   Slang. Marvelously excellent.

[Blend of fantastic and fabulous.]

   "At last week's Polo for the Pops benefit in Fort Worth, your humble
   scribe here played opposite developer Ed Bass in a polo match at the
   Upchurch family's fantabulous Brushy Creek Polo Ranch."
   Alan Peppard, It's a Wynne - Wynne - Wynne situation,
   The Dallas Morning News, Jun 9, 1996.

